Nigeria’s leading radio station, 99.3 Nigeria Info, has hinted at plans to build a formidable sports-broadcast army through the launch of the third edition of the “Femi and The Gang Fan Battle.” This is in a bid to create a platform that provides sports-loving Nigerians with an avenue to showcase their in-depth knowledge on football-related topics.   64 teams jostle for N2m in Akindele football tourney     Milo School Basketball Championship finals kicks off     Sarri wants Okereke in Lazio   The “Femi and The Gang Fan Battle” is a competition that seeks to strengthen the friendly sports ecosystem across the country by providing Nigerian youths with the opportunity to engage with one another through intelligent debates on the exciting game of football while the winner clinches the grand prize of a million naira. The competition further aims to serve as a launch pad for a new generation of sports broadcasters who will raise the bar of sports journalism nationwide. Commenting on the launch of the competition, Femi Obong-Daniels, the General Manager and Group Head of Sports for Cool FM, Wazobia FM, and Nigeria Info, noted that the  provides football lovers with an opportunity to demonstrate their passion for the sports.